        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>5000
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>, 9100
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>, 9200
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>, 9400
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    and 9900
                    <emph type="italic">i</emph>
                    Models built before September 8, 1999 with aero mirrors, Code 16WRW and 16WRV, may experience a
                    reduction in the transmission and reception of CB radio signals because the CB antenna used with the
                    aero mirror system does not have an adequate ground.
                </para>
                <para>To improve CB radio transmission and reception, Navistar has developed a ground strap kit that is
                    available through the Parts Distribution Center (PDC).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If the CB antenna is not grounded, it could lead to CB radio performance degradation over
                            time.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
